    <p>
      We solve two different initial value problems using power series.
    </p>

    <p>
      <ol marker="a.">
        <li>
          <p>
            Consider the IVP given by 
            <me>
              y' = 2xy, \ y(0) = 1
            </me>.
          </p>
          <p>
            <ol marker="i.">
              <li>
                <p>
                  Let <m>y</m> be given by the power series 
                  <me>
                    y = c_0 + c_1 x + c_2 x^2 + c_3 x^3 + c_4 x^4 + \cdots + c_n x^n + \cdots
                  </me>.
                  Find expressions for both <m>y'</m> and <m>2xy</m>.
              </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Consider Airy's equation with initial conditions given by 
            <me>
              y'' - xy = 0, \ y(0) = 1, \ y'(0) = 0
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
